<font color="#FF0000">TREADING WATER IN A RIVER</font><br>
<tt>Thu Aug 14 23:55:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Humming Eagle,<br><br>
I went back to the &quot;Vietnam Protest&quot; string yesterday, and now understand what has upset you.  Please note that Doc Spatz may be reacting as he is because I and some others called him on what sounded like racist writings of his concerning the Vietnamese community in the United States.  We did get him to see the Vietnamese Americans in a different light, at least temporarily.  <br><br>
Since I was only following this string for the last month or so, I missed out on some of the fireworks as they were occurring.  <br><br>
I think, for myself, that I will now stay away from that &quot;greased pig contest&quot; for awhile more, and just see where it goes.  <br><br>
Sometimes, when you're in a river current, it's best just to tread water an see where it leads.  Then take advantage of the rocks and eddies, and let the water take you where you wish to go, without the effort of swimming hard.
